# Preferred tools and packages

Prefer this stack for new work. **Repository READMEs and pkg.go.dev** are authoritative for APIs, versions, and breaking changes‚Äîrefresh from there before major upgrades.

Day-to-day **formatting and lint commands** (including when to run `--fix`) are summarized in **`go-style.mdc`**; this file focuses on *what* to prefer.

---

## Toolchain

### godev (primary CLI)

Use **[godev](https://github.com/jkaveri/godev)** as the unified CLI for the full Go development loop when the project supports it: build, test, lint, mocks, modules, coverage, CI helpers, and more.

- **Docs:** [README on GitHub](https://github.com/jkaveri/godev/blob/main/README.md) (or `godev/README.md` in a local clone). **Subcommands, flags, and behavior** are defined there‚Äîdo not guess; read or run `--help`.
- **Install:** `go install github.com/jkaveri/godev/cmd/godev@latest`
- **Discoverability:** `godev --help`, `godev <command> --help`. Root flags include `--no-color` (also `NO_COLOR`, `GODEV_NO_COLOR`).
- **Typical commands** (see README for the full list): `build`, `changed`, `ci`, `test` (including config generation), `lint` (including **golangci-lint config generation**), `clean`, `mod`, `mock`, `work`, `version`, `coverprofile`, `release`, `github-release`, `commit`.

Fall back to plain `go`, `make`, or project scripts when `godev` is not adopted.

### Linting: golangci-lint (via godev)

- **golangci-lint** is the preferred linter aggregator.
- Prefer invoking it through **`godev lint`** when available so versions and config stay aligned with the team.
- To **bootstrap or regenerate** `.golangci.yml`, use **`godev lint golangci-config`** (or the equivalent documented in the godev README), then tune `linters`, `formatters`, and `exclusions` for the module.

### Formatting: gofumpt and golines (via golangci-lint)

- Prefer **gofumpt** and **golines** for formatting style (stricter than `gofmt` alone; line-length handling for long signatures and calls).
- Run them **through the repo‚Äôs golangci-lint setup** (e.g. `formatters` in `.golangci.yml`) or **`godev lint -f`** / the project‚Äôs documented fix command‚Äîavoid one-off manual invocations unless the README says otherwise.

## Verification

- Prefer **`godev lint`** / **`godev ci`** when available; otherwise follow CI and `go vet ./...`.
- Keep `.golangci.yml` aligned with **`godev lint golangci-config`** when you generate or refresh config.

## `go.mod` / `go.work`

When editing module files, run tidy and verify builds‚Äîdo not hand-edit `replace` directives without reviewing impact on consumers.
